- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a decoding algorithm for the constructed code.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper may have applications in distributed computing where data may be transmitted with errors.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper may have applications in network communication where errors may occur.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper may discuss the complexity of constructing and decoding the proposed code.
